tal_blocking":0},"body":"### Problem\n\nIn diff mode, nvim aborts with ``src/nvim/drawline.c:2051: win_line: Assertion `extra_attr_next >= 0' failed.``\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/db702782e0168d45256a975c4bc1809b5785d952/src/nvim/drawline.c#L2051\n\nwhen\n\n- foldtext has non latin1 characters, i.e. `LANG=ja_JP.UTF-8` or `uk_UA.UTF-8`; nvim works fine with `en_US.UTF-8`\n- one of lines around diff is sufficiently long (length > 2×window width?)\n\nThe text seems to be translated in Japanese and Ukrainian only:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/db702782e0168d45256a975c4bc1809b5785d952/src/nvim/po/ja.po#L3552-L3555\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/db702782e0168d45256a975c4bc1809b5785d952/src/nvim/po/uk.po#L3581-L3586\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nGenerate locale of `ja_JP.UTF-8` or `uk_UA.UTF-8`.\nBuild nvim with `ENABLE_TRANSLATIONS` ON.\nPrepare files:\n```sh\n{ yes | head -n 8; echo 123456789 123456789 123456789 123456789 123456789 123456789 ; } > foo.txt\nyes | head -n 9 > bar.txt\n```\n\nSet the terminal size to 80×24 and `LANG` to `ja_JP.UTF-8` or `uk_UA.UTF-8`, then `nvim -d --clean foo.txt bar.txt` and `G$`.\n\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/L1ME60May1XnRgaLwSPnCELCA.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/L1ME60May1XnRgaLwSPnCELCA)\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo assertion failure occurs.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\ndb702782e0168d45256a975c4bc1809b5785d952\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1362\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.56.1 using VTE 0.80.1 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo","closed_by":{"login":"zeertzjq","id":35768171,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1NzY4MTcx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/35768171?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/zeertzjq","html_url":"https://github.com/zeertzjq","followers_url":"https://api.gith